items.summary: Split archive file created by File Splitter & Joiner (FFSJ), a utility used to break up files into smaller parts and reconstruct them; contains the first part of a multi-part encrypted archive; used for storing password-protected data in smaller segments.

Renamed Microsoft Word Document
items.summary: A _DOCX file is a Microsoft Word document with the .docx extension changed to ._docx. It is a .DOCX file, which includes formatted text, images, graphs, tables, and charts. _DOCX files may be renamed to ._docx files by an email program to prevent the file from being blocked by an email service.

Google Play Music ID File
items.summary: A _PLAYMUSICID file is a data file used to identify the account of a Google Play Music user. It contains a unique string of identifying characters and is stored on an external storage card connected to an Android device.

Unix Shared Library File
items.summary: Library or library link file used by Linux operating systems; appends the .0 extension to the name of the original library file, which has the .SO extension; either contains a library or a reference link to another library on the system.

items.name: Indexing Service Data File
items.summary: An 000 file is a data file created by Indexing Service, a software component of the Windows operating system that creates a searchable file system index from files on the hard drive. The data stored in a 000 file helps Windows perform quick searches.

items.name: What are 001 files and how to open them
7-Zip Split Archive Part 2 File
items.summary: A 7Z.002 file is the second part of a multi-volume .7Z archive. It must always be paired with an accompanying .7Z.001 file to extract the files it contains. If the 7Z.002 file is part of a large multi-volume archive, it must also be matched with additional 7Z.### files (7Z.003, 7Z.004, and so on).

items.name: Split Archive Part 3
items.summary: A 003 file is the third part of a split archive, which was likely created by an archiving utility such as 7-Zip or Incredible Bee Archiver. It should be accompanied by a .001 and .002 file, and it may also be accompanied by successive .### files. These files contain the split archive's other parts.

0CC-FamiTracker Module
items.summary: An 0CC file is a module used by 0CC-FamiTracker, a backwards compatible extension of the FamiTracker program used to produce music for Nintendo (NES) Famicom systems. It contains module data such as instruments and patterns, which are notes that comprise the melody.

F-Secure Renamed Virus File
items.summary: Virus file detected by F-Secure, an antivirus program; stores a renamed .EXE file that has a virus which could not be disinfected; renamed from an EXE file to an OXE file so that a virus will not execute when double-clicking it in Windows.

Iomega Disk Backup
items.summary: A 113 file is a backup file created by Iomega Backup or Iomega Automatic Backup Pro. It contains a copy of the data stored on a Zip or Jaz disk. Typically, the Iomega backup utility used to create a 113 file can be used to restore that file to a Zip or Jaz disk.

items.name: Lotus 1-2-3 Spreadsheet
items.summary: A 123 file is a spreadsheet created by Lotus 1-2-3, or exported by another spreadsheet program, such as Corel Quattro Pro. It stores data in rows and columns and supports functions that can be applied to the data in various cells, which can automatically populate the data in other cells. 123 files may contain various spreadsheets, such as financial budgets and quarterly earnings.

items.name: Autodesk 123D Drawing
items.summary: CAD drawing created by 123D, a free 3D CAD design application provided by Autodesk; may contain multiple parts that together comprise the model; can be published to standard raster image formats or to Autodesk's .DWG format.

items.name: 123D Design Model File
items.summary: 3D model created by 123D Design, a program used for designing models for print or fabrication; stores the 3D geometry of the model, as well as materials that define the surface appearance of the model.

items.name: Lotus 1-2-3 SmartMaster File
items.summary: A 12M file is a spreadsheet created by Lotus 1-2-3, which is part of IBM Lotus SmartSuite. It contains a pre-designed spreadsheet that allows a user to enter information to create forecasts, financial statements, and budgets. 12M files also include formulas, formatting, and print ranges.

Android Gallery Thumbnail Index
items.summary: A THUMBDATA4-1763508120 file is a data file created by the Gallery app included with select Android phones, such as the Samsung J7 and HTC Desire SV. It contains information about every thumbnail image Gallery has indexed, to help the app load the images more quickly. THUMBDATA4-1763508120 is stored in a device's hidden .THUMBNAILS folder, which is visible only when you've chosen to show hidden files and folders on your device.

items.name: 2017 StudioTax Return File
items.summary: A 17T file is a tax return created by the 2017 version of StudioTax, a Windows and macOS program used to prepare personal income tax returns in Canada. It contains all the necessary Canadian federal and province tax information and personal data entered by the user.

items.name: What are 19 files and how to open them
Android Gallery Thumbnail Index
items.summary: A THUMBDATA3--1967290299 file is a data file created by the Gallery app included with select Android phones, such as HTC Desire SV and Sony Xperia. It contains information about every thumbnail image Gallery has indexed, to help the app load the images more quickly. THUMBDATA3--1967290299 is stored in a device's hidden .THUMBNAILS folder, which is visible only when you've chosen to show hidden files and folders on your device.

What are 1P2 files and how to open them
TurboTax Form File
items.summary: A 1PE file is a form used by the Windows version of Intuit TurboTax, an application for preparing U.S. taxes. It stores data for displaying tax forms within the software and includes form text and layout information. 1PE files may also contain instructions that may be included with each form.

items.name: Bio-Rad Quantity One Gel Image
items.summary: A 1SC file is an image created by Bio-Rad Quantity One, a gel electrophoresis result analyzer. It contains a digital copy of a gel electrophoresis result. 1SC files are used to analyze results and share them with other Bio-Rad users.

items.name: Readme File
items.summary: Readme text file sometimes bundled with applications; contains important information or instructions for operating the software; uses the "1st" extension so that users know to open the readme first before running the application for the first time.

items.name: 1tracker Instrument
items.summary: A 1TI file is an instrument specification used by 1tracker, a music tracker for Windows and Linux. It defines an instrument's note length and threshold. 1tracker users can create and load 1TI files in the program's Instrument Editor.

items.name: 1tracker Module
items.summary: A 1TM file is an audio module created by 1tracker, a music tracker for Windows and Linux. It contains plain text information that defines the song the module contains, the instrument(s) used to play the song, and various song metadata. When opened in 1tracker, 1TM files appear as a grid that shows a song's channels and notes.

items.name: Unix Section 2 Manual Page
items.summary: A 2 file contains a Unix manual page (man page) that describes a system call. Each 2 file is named for the system call it describes. 2 files are meant to be opened and viewed using the Unix man utility.

ASUS Notebook BIOS 208 Update File
items.summary: BIOS update file used to "flash" the BIOS to ASUS computers running Windows; contains settings and instructions for the "208" BIOS update, which is intended to update the Embedded Controller (EC) firmware on an ASUS notebook motherboard.

Descent 2 Color Palette
items.summary: A 256 file is a color palette file used by Descent 2, a first-person shooter in which players pilot a spaceship to destroy mines infected by a computer virus. It contains a list of RGB values that describe colors used by the textures stored in an associated .PIG file. 256 files use the same name as their associated PIG file.

Super Audio CD Two-Channel Audio
items.summary: A 2CH file is a two-channel audio file that was likely included on a Super Audio CD (SACD). It contains a song that was ripped from a Super Audio CD or downloaded from a digital music marketplace. 2CH files are stereo versions of associated .DFF files.

items.name: What are 2CO files and how to open them
VersaCAD 2D Drawing File
items.summary: A 2D file is a two-dimensional (2D) drawing created by Archway Systems VersaCAD, a CAD program used for drafting and dimensioning. It contains objects, lines, shapes, and measurements, and other details of 2D representations of buildings and components in a proprietary binary format.

items.name: What are 2DF files and how to open them
Puppy Linux Save State File
items.summary: Operating system (OS) snapshot saved by Puppy Linux, an easy-to-use Linux variant; stores the state of the OS at a point in time and can be used for resetting the OS back to that state; saved to an external file system partition, since Puppy Linux can run standalone off of a CD or .ISO file.

items.name: Apple IIGS Disk Image
items.summary: Disk image created from a floppy disk formatted for the Apple IIGS, a 16-bit Apple II computer; may contain applications, games, or other files that can be used by an Apple IIGS system.

items.name: Nintendo DS Sound File
items.summary: Game audio file used by some Nintendo DS games; saves audio data in a format similar to MIDI; can be played by Winamp or Foobar2000 with the vio2sf plug-in.

items.name: What are 2TS files and how to open them
Unix Section 3 Manual Page
items.summary: A 3 file is a Unix manual page (man page) that describes a library function. You can read a 3 file's contents using the Unix man utility. Each 3 file is named for the function it documents.
